}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 7 February 2024
|update = Poll 80 Wilderness Changes & More
|change = Leviathan's lightning attack now launches 1 tick later if the player is above 25 HP, consistent with its behaviour prior to the [[31 January]] [[2024]] game [[Update:Scurrius & DT2 Combat Achievements|update]].
}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 31 January 2024
|update = Scurrius & DT2 Combat Achievements
|change = [[Combat Achievements]] were added for the boss.
}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 16 August 2023
|update = Desert Treasure II Changes & More
|change = 
* The Leviathan's orb projectiles will no longer hit through protection prayers between the beginning of the enrage phase and the spawning of the [[abyssal pathfinder]].
* The Leviathan will now drop [[brimstone key]]s in an accessible location upon death, rather than where it spawns.
* Personal best kill times for the Leviathan will now broadcast in [[clan chat]] and [[group ironman]] channels.
}}
{{Subject changes
|update = Desert Treasure II - Further Changes
|date = 9 August 2023
|change = 
* Players will no longer receive the {{mes|Your melee attacks can't reach the lure!}} message when trying to [[autocast]] in [[melee]] range.
* The colour of the melee projectiles has been adjusted to be clearer for players with visual impairments.
* [[Shadow spells]] now grant the base [[experience]] when cast on the Leviathan.
* An issue causing perfect kills to fail has been resolved.
}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 3 August 2023
|update = Desert Treasure II - Tweaks and Drop Rates
|change = 
* The combat level for the quest variant was increased from 574 to 593.
* The drop rate for the tradeable unique drop table was increased from 1/120 to 1/96.
}}
{{Subject changes footer}}

==Trivia==
*The {{wp|Leviathan}} is a mythical creature referenced extensively in the Bible and is associated with the sin of envy.
*Its design appears to be based on a {{RSL|Raw rocktail|rocktail}}, a cave-dwelling fish from ''RuneScape'', both the {{RSL|Raw rocktail|raw}} and {{RSL|Rocktail|cooked}} version.
*The Leviathan is the only Desert Treasure 2 boss which is aggressive towards players upon spawning:
**[[Duke Sucellus]] is in a sleeping state and is not aggressive until awakened with poison.
**[[Vardorvis]] does not attack players when entering his arena nor when he respawns, since his barrier mechanic does not trigger until he is attacked.
**[[The Whisperer]], while as an Odd Figure, does focus on the player, but she cannot attack in that state and is a separate NPC.

* The Leviathan is the only Desert Treasure 2 boss to not have a lore reason for returning back to life after every kill:
** Duke Sucellus is not killed by the player, merely subdued after which he falls back asleep.
** Vardorvis' body is reanimated by [[the Strangler]].
** The Whisperer is reanimated by the power of [[Ancient Pillar (Desert Treasure II)|the Ancient Pillar]].

* The Leviathan is the only Desert Treasure 2 Boss to not be a member of [[Zarosian Empire|the Zarosian Empire]].
* While this Leviathan had adapted to the abyss, a leviathan in its natural state is a [[rsw:Crassian_Leviathan|boss]] in ''RuneScape.''

* The Leviathan may be inspired by a similar fight in the Drakengard series.
* Unlike most monsters, the Leviathan's normal mode encounter provides more slayer experience than its health suggests. This is not the case with its Awakened variant.

